Zephyr RTOS Setup for Microcontrollers: Step-by-Step Guide
✅ 1. Install Prerequisites
✅ 2. Create Zephyr Project and Initialize
✅ 3. Export Zephyr Environment Variables
✅ 4. Install Toolchain (Zephyr SDK or GNU Arm Embedded)
✅ 5. Install Python Dependencies
✅ 6. Build an Example Application
✅ 7. Flash the Binary to the Microcontroller
✅ 8. Optional: Run Menuconfig for Configuration


Do you have to activate a Python virtual-environment?
Strictly speaking, no. Zephyr’s build system is CMake + Ninja and a cross-compiler tool-chain; those parts are not Python-dependent.
However, all of Zephyr’s helper tools (west, Kconfig/Devicetree linters, documentation scripts, etc.) are Python packages. Installing them in a virtual environment keeps their versions separate from anything else you use on the same P


Typical first-time setup (Linux/macOS)
=================================================================================
# 1) Pick a workspace directory
mkdir -p ~/zephyrproject
cd ~/zephyrproject

# 2) Create and activate a venv
python3 -m venv .venv
source .venv/bin/activate      # Your prompt shows (.venv)

# 3) Install West inside the venv
pip install --upgrade pip west

# 4) Fetch Zephyr and its modules
west init -l zephyr            # or just `west init` for a clean clone
west update

# 5) Make Zephyr visible to CMake and install Python deps
west zephyr-export
west packages pip --install    # same as: pip install -r zephyr/scripts/requirements.txt

# 6. (Optional) Download and install the Zephyr SDK plus the Arm toolchain
west sdk install -t arm-zephyr-eabi
(Downloads the pre-built Zephyr SDK bundle (compiler, linker, objcopy, etc.) for all supported architectures—or only the ones you request with -t arm-zephyr-eabi, -t riscv64-zephyr-elf, and so on.)
(Runs its setup script and then sets ZEPHYR_SDK_INSTALL_DIR and ZEPHYR_TOOLCHAIN_VARIANT=zephyr in your shell rc file so west build can find the tools automatically.)


first-time Windows setup that places your Zephyr workspace in D:\zephyr_project
==================================================================================================
# 1. Make the workspace and move into it
New-Item -Path D:\zephyr_project -ItemType Directory
Set-Location   D:\zephyr_project

# 2. Create and activate a Python virtual environment
python   -m venv .venv
.venv\Scripts\Activate.ps1        # use .venv\Scripts\activate.bat in cmd.exe

# 3. Upgrade pip and install the West meta-tool
python   -m pip install --upgrade pip
pip install west

# 4. Clone Zephyr and all declared modules
west init   -m https://github.com/zephyrproject-rtos/zephyr
west update

# 5. Register Zephyr with CMake so west build can find it
west zephyr-export

# 6. Pull in every Python package required by Zephyr and its modules
west packages pip --install

# 7. (Optional) Download and install the Zephyr SDK plus the Arm toolchain
west sdk install -t arm-zephyr-eabi


1) Install dependencies
winget install Kitware.CMake Ninja-build.Ninja oss-winget.gperf python Git.Git oss-winget.dtc wget 7zip.7zip

2) Get Zephyr and install Python dependencies
Create a new virtual environment:
python -m venv zephyrproject\.venv
zephyrproject\.venv\Scripts\Activate.ps1
pip install west
west init zephyrproject
cd zephyrproject
west update
Export a Zephyr CMake package. This allows CMake to automatically load boilerplate code required for building Zephyr applications.

west zephyr-export
west packages pip --install

3) Install the Zephyr SDK
cd $Env:HOMEPATH\zephyrproject\zephyr
west sdk install



Build and run command 
===========================================================
Build the Hello World sample for an emulated board
west build -b qemu_x86   zephyr/samples/hello_world

-b qemu_x86 selects the x86 QEMU board definition.

You can pick any other QEMU target Zephyr ships, for example

qemu_cortex_m3 (Arm Cortex-M3)

qemu_riscv32 (32-bit RISC-V)

qemu_x86_64 (64-bit x86)

Run the built image inside QEMU
============================================
west build -t run

or single command west build -b qemu_x86 -t run zephyr/samples/hello_world



as per getting started guide 
================================================================================
Get Zephyr and Install Python Dependencies
powershell
Copy
Edit
# Create project directory
mkdir D:\zephyrproject
cd D:\zephyrproject

# Create and activate virtual environment
python -m venv .venv
.venv\Scripts\Activate.ps1

# Install West and initialize Zephyr workspace
pip install west
west init -m https://github.com/zephyrproject-rtos/zephyr

cd zephyrproject
west update

# Export Zephyr CMake package (required for build)
west zephyr-export

# Install all required Python packages
west packages pip --install
pip install -r zephyr/scripts/requirements.txt
